A motorcyclist has been injured after his bike collided with a car in the south side of Glasgow. Motorcyclist hurt in collision with car in Glasgow A motorcyclist has been injured after his bike collided with a car in the south side of Glasgow.
Emergency services were called to the scene in Polmadie Road, off Aitkenhead Road, near Toryglen, at about 05:50.
A spokesman for Police Scotland said the injured biker was taken by ambulance to hospital. The male car driver was uninjured.
The road has been closed while traffic officers carry out investigations into the crash. Diversions are in place.
 